questions.article:
​​​​​​​
The graph shows the height above ground, in meters, of a ball x seconds after the ball was launched upward from a platform. Which statement is the best interpretation of the marked point  (1.0, 3.9) in this context?

options.name: A
options.content: 1.0 second after being launched, the ball's height above ground is 3.9 meters.

options.name: B
options.content: 3.9 seconds after being launched, the ball's height above ground is 1.0 meter.

options.name: C
options.content: The ball was launched from an initial height of 1.0 meter with an initial velocity of 3.9 meters per second.

options.name: D
options.content: The ball was launched from an initial height of 3.9 meter with an initial velocity of 1.0 meters per second.

questions.correct: 1.0 second after being launched, the ball's height above ground is 3.9 meters.

questions.article: In one week in 2017, a technician earned a total of $700 by working at her regular job and at a second job doing part-time work. The equation 16h+13c=700  represents this situation, where h is the number of hours worked at her regular job and c is the number of hours worked at her second job. Which of the following is the best interpretation of 16 in this context?

options.name: A
options.content: The amount, in dollars, the technician earned for each hour she worked at her regular job

options.name: B
options.content: The amount, in dollars, the technician earned for each hour she worked at her second job

options.name: C
options.content: The number of hours the technician worked in one week at her regular job

options.name: D
options.content: The number of hours the technician worked in one week at her second job

questions.correct: The amount, in dollars, the technician earned for each hour she worked at her regular job

options.name: B
